  <!-- WHAT IS A CP12 -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What Is a Gas Safety Certificate (CP12)?</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">A CP12 is the official document issued by a Gas Safe registered engineer following a gas safety inspection. It is the only document that satisfies the legal obligation under the Gas Safety Regulations 1998.</p>

      <div class="pf-card pf-card-navy" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h3>What a Gas Safety Certificate Confirms</h3>
        <p>A CP12 gas safety certificate confirms that all gas appliances, pipework, flues and ventilation in a rental property have been inspected by a Gas Safe registered engineer and found to be safe for continued use. It records the date of inspection, the engineer's Gas Safe registration number, every appliance checked, its location and the result of each check.</p>
        <p>The CP12 was introduced under the <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/landlords/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safety (Installation and Use) Regulations 1998</a> and is the legal standard for gas safety compliance in rental properties across England, Scotland and Wales. It must be renewed every 12 months and can only be issued by a <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safe registered engineer</a>. It cannot be issued by a general plumber, electrician or any other trade.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pf-card pf-card-orange" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h3>Gas Safety Certificate vs Boiler Service. What Is the Difference?</h3>
        <p>A gas safety certificate is a legal safety inspection. It checks that appliances are safe but does not clean, maintain or service the boiler. A boiler service is a maintenance check that keeps the boiler operating efficiently and is required annually by manufacturers to keep the warranty valid. They are two completely separate things and both are needed every year.</p>
        <p>Combining both on the same visit costs £175 and saves time, coordination and cost compared to booking them separately. Most Liverpool landlords who work with us book the combined visit annually.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

