  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Gas Safety Certificate Liverpool. Your Questions Answered</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Straight answers to what Liverpool landlords and homeowners ask most before booking.</p>
      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does a gas safety certificate cost in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A CP12 gas safety certificate costs £80 for the first gas appliance, with additional appliances at £10 each. A combined gas safety certificate and annual boiler service costs £175 in a single visit. The <a href="https://www.checkatrade.com/blog/cost-guides/gas-safety-certificate-cost/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Checkatrade average for Liverpool is £76 to £108</a>. No call-out fee and no hidden charges on any visit.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">LEGAL</span>&nbsp; Is a gas safety certificate a legal requirement for Liverpool landlords?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Under the <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/landlords/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safety (Installation and Use) Regulations 1998</a>, every landlord in England must hold a valid CP12 for every rental property with gas appliances. The certificate must be renewed every 12 months. Landlords must provide a copy to existing tenants within 28 days and to new tenants before they move in. Non-compliance risks fines up to £6,000 per property.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">SECTION 21</span>&nbsp; Does a lapsed gas safety certificate affect a Section 21 notice?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. A landlord who has not provided a valid gas safety certificate to their tenant may be unable to serve a valid Section 21 notice to regain possession. Courts have ruled that compliance with gas safety obligations is a legal prerequisite for a valid Section 21. A lapsed or unserved CP12 can prevent eviction proceedings entirely. Annual renewal and correct service of the certificate to tenants are critical for landlords who may ever need to rely on Section 21.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">RECORDS</span>&nbsp; How long do I need to keep a gas safety certificate?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Landlords must keep a record of the gas safety inspection for a minimum of two years from the date of issue and must be able to produce it to the HSE, local authority or a tenant on request. We email the digital certificate the same day, creating a permanent timestamped record. We recommend storing all CP12 certificates in a dedicated folder organised by property.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">TENANTS</span>&nbsp; Can tenants request a copy of the gas safety certificate?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Tenants have a legal right to receive a copy of the gas safety certificate. Landlords must provide a copy to existing tenants within 28 days of issue and to new tenants before they move in. If a tenant requests a copy and does not receive one, they can report the landlord to the HSE or their local authority. We email the certificate directly so you can forward it to tenants on the same day.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">RENEWAL</span>&nbsp; Is there a grace period for renewing a gas safety certificate?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. If the inspection is carried out between 10 and 12 months after the previous inspection, the new certificate runs from the expiry date of the old one rather than the inspection date. This means you do not lose the full 12 months of coverage. For example, if your certificate expires on 1 October and the inspection is carried out on 15 September, the new certificate will still run until 1 October the following year. This allows you to renew slightly early without shortening the validity period.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">DIFFERENCE</span>&nbsp; What is the difference between a gas safety certificate and a boiler service?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A gas safety certificate (CP12) is a legal safety inspection confirming all gas appliances are safe. It does not service or maintain the boiler. A boiler service is a maintenance check that keeps the boiler running efficiently and is required annually by manufacturers to keep the warranty valid. Both are needed every year. We offer them combined for £175 in a single visit.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">FAULTS</span>&nbsp; What happens if an appliance fails the inspection?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>We follow the Gas Industry Unsafe Situations Procedure. An Immediately Dangerous appliance will be turned off and disconnected before we leave. An At Risk fault will be noted and a written repair quote provided. We never start repair work without your approval. A certificate cannot be issued until all Immediately Dangerous faults are resolved.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">SAME DAY</span>&nbsp; Can I get a same-day gas safety certificate in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes, subject to availability. We offer same-day CP12 inspections across Liverpool and Merseyside. Call us on 0151 558 0334 to check availability. The digital certificate is emailed the same day on completion. For a gas emergency, call Cadent Gas on 0800 111 999 first.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Ideal Plumbing Solutions is Gas Safe registered. Verify at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. It is a legal requirement for any engineer issuing a CP12 to be Gas Safe registered. All inspections are carried out by our own directly employed engineers. We never use sub-contractors.</p></div></details>
      </div>
